HEADWORD: Trendle
<hw>Tren"dle</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[AS.
<ets>trendel</ets>, <ets>tryndel</ets>, circle, ring. See
<er>Trend</er>, <pos>v. i.</pos>, and cf. <er>Trundle</er>.]</ety>
<def>A wheel, spindle, or the like; a trundle.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The shaft the wheel, the wheel, the <qex>trendle</qex> turns.</q>
<rj><qau>Sylvester.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Trennel</ent>⟦br⟧
